The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Thursday, July 17, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Thursday, July 17, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	AJC Bose Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, due to work on the flyover. Buses to Alipore will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-AJC Bose Road route. Those travelling towards Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route.				 																																	Esplanade. Samajwadi Chhatra Sabha members will hold a sit-in off the Metro station to protest Left Front activities.				 																Shakespeare film				 																																	Peter Brooks King Lear will be screened at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre at 6 pm.				 																Monsoon music				 																																	Borsha Mongal, a monsoon festival featuring modern Bengali songs, at MusicWorld from 5 pm.				 																Animation talk				 																																	A discussion on Role of animation and special effects in media and entertainment at Kala Mandir from 4 pm. Participants include Gautam Ghose, Chiranjeet and Chandi Lahiri.
